content.text: Find the positive value of \(p\) when \(V=3200\) and \(m=2\).
Write these lengths in order of size, starting with the smallest.
Work out the area of the trapezium.
Write down the inequality for \(x\) represented on the number line.
Work out the expected number of games she wins.
Pryanka plays a game in which she can win, lose or draw.
The table shows the probability of her winning or losing a game.
By writing each number correct to 1 significant figure, work out an estimate for \(D\).
Three regular polygons \(A, B\) and \(C\) meet at a point.
The interior angles of the polygons are in the ratio \(a: b: c = 3: 4: 5\).
Show that polygon \(C\) has twice the number of sides as polygon \(B\).
(a) In April, \(\frac{17}{20}\) of the company's sales were on the website.
(b) In February, the company had sales of \(\$ 3.5\) million.
A company sells items either on a website or in shops.
The composite bar chart shows the percentage of sales on the website and in shops for January, February and March.
On the grid, draw the bar for April.
Work out the value of sales in shops in February.
(a) Write as a single fraction in its simplest form.
Give a geometrical reason for your answer.
The diagram shows a cylinder with radius \(r \text{ cm}\) and height 16 cm.
The volume of the cylinder is equal to the volume of the sphere.
\(A, B, C, D\) and \(E\) lie on a circle. \(FG\) is a tangent to the circle at \(C\). Angle \(B A D=110^{\circ}\), angle \(A D B=20^{\circ}\) and angle \(B E C=45^{\circ}\).
Find the perimeter of the quadrilateral \(A C D E\).
Give your answer in the form \(p+k \sqrt{q}\).
The quadrilateral \(A C D E\) is formed by two right-angled triangles \(A B E\) and \(B C D\). \(A C=17 \mathrm{~cm}, A E=18 \mathrm{~cm}\) and \(B D=6 \mathrm{~cm}\).
In the Venn diagram, shade the region \((A \cup B \cup C)'\).
Write down the coordinates of the point where the graph of \(y=5 x-3\) crosses the \(y-\) axis.
By sketching the graph of \(y=x^{3}+x^{2}-x\), determine whether the stationary point \(\left(\frac{1}{3},-\frac{5}{27}\right)\) is a maximum or a minimum.
\(A\) is the point \((1,7)\) and \(B\) is the point \((5,15)\).
Find the equation of the perpendicular bisector of the line \(A B\).Give your answer in the form \(y=m x+c\).
The curve has a stationary point at \(\left(\frac{1}{3},-\frac{5}{27}\right)\).
Question 23 is printed on the next page.
The equation \(x^{3}+x^{2}-x=k\) has fewer than 3 solutions.
Find the range of possible values for \(k\).
